nd and outbound dependencies. Time management – using the right planning tools, balancing work versus meetings. Failure – handling the blame game, protecting the team, rescuing the project. This book condenses into a handy summary much of the information and advice that can be found in project management related books and discussion forums. It is an ideal reference for anyone involved in IT project management, from professional service organisations (PSO) and project management offices (PMO), through to active project managers and studying graduates.  Buy this book and deliver your next project on time, on budget and to specification  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aDiagnotic imaging -- Congresses. 0aImaging systems in medicine -- Congresses. 0aInformation technology projectsxManagement. 0aInformation technologyxManagement. 0aManagement information systems. 7aCOMPUTERS / Desktop Applications / Project Management Software.2bisacsh  aIT project management.  aIT project manager.  aprofessional service organisations.  aproject management challenges.  aproject management office.  aproject management.  aproject manager.  aproject scope.1 aDoraiswamy, Premanand, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz978184928343440uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9781849283427  aGBV-deGruyter-alles